quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  71,1,"We sent Noah to his people, saying: \"Give warning to your people before there comes to them a painful punishment"
  71,2,"He said: \"O my People! I am sent towards you as a plain Warner"
  71,3,"Worship Allah, fear Him and obey me"
  71,4,"If you will do so, He will forgive you your sins and give you respite for an appointed term. The fact is that when the term given by Allah arrives, it cannot be deferred. If you could understand"
  71,5,"After exhausting all his efforts Noah said: \"O Lord! I have pleaded with my people night and day"
  71,6,but my plea has only added to their aversion
  71,7,"Each time I called on them to seek Your pardon, they thrust their fingers in their ears and drew their cloaks over their heads, persisting in sin and puffing themselves up with insolent pride"
  71,8,I have called them aloud
  71,9,appealed them openly in public and secretly in private
  71,10,"saying: \"Seek forgiveness of your Lord, He is ever ready to forgive you"
  71,11,He will send abundant rain for you from heaven
  71,12,"help you with wealth and sons, and provide you with gardens and the flowing rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you do not regard the greatness of Allah
  71,14,when He has created you in gradual stages
  71,15,Can you not see how Allah created the seven heavens one above the other
  71,16,placing in them the moon as a light and the sun as a glorious lamp
  71,17,Allah has caused you to grow as a growth from the earth
  71,18,He will return you to the same earth and then raise you back to life again on the Day of Resurrection
  71,19,Allah has made the earth for you as a wide expanse
  71,20,so that you may walk in its spacious paths